<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:8.0pt; text-align:left">
<span style="">The Chair introduced the agenda item and noted that
the Committee had looked at the first set of savings proposals at
its meeting in November 2025 and the Council remained in a very
challenging financial position. The Committee was asked to review
an updated set of savings proposals at this meeting and consider
whether the Council would be able to close the funding gap and
would the results still allow for Lambeth&rsquo;s services to
deliver to the standard expected by residents.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:8.0pt; text-align:left">
<span style="">The <a name="x__Hlk214554171" id=
"x__Hlk214554171">Acting Cabinet Member for Finance</a>, Councillor
Judith Cavanagh introduced the report and noted that:</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top:0cm">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:left"><span style="">The
report contained an additional set of savings that were necessary
<span class="GramE">in light of</span> the financial pressures on
the Council&rsquo;s budget. It was noted that those financial
pressures continued to be experienced in the Council&rsquo;s larger
service areas such as provisions for those in temporary
accommodation, Adult Social Care and Children's
Services.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:left"><span style="">While
the Council was facing those financial pressures, it was still
performing well and was delivering a good quality of service. This
was demonstrated by the &lsquo;Good&rsquo; rating that was achieved
recently by the borough&rsquo;s Youth Justice Service.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:left"><span style="">The
Government&rsquo;s commitment to supporting local authorities to
deliver for their residents was demonstrated by providing them with
multi-year financial settlements to help them plan more effectively
for the future. The Council was pleased that it had received a
larger financial settlement from the Government than had been
predicted, but it was still not sufficient to bridge the funding
gap, therefore, they would be lobbying the Government for further
additional financial support. The Council had been granted a
transition arrangement of three years to help it improve its
financial position, but this may be inhibited by the fact it was
one of four local authorities that had been &lsquo;capped&rsquo; by
the <span class="GramE">Government,</span> therefore the four local
authorities were in discussions with Ministers regarding this
matter.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:left"><span style="">It was
refreshing that there was finally a <span class=
"GramE">Government</span> in place that was committed to improve
the lives for the country&rsquo;s citizens and their commitment to
lift the two-child limit which restricted the additional support
for children on Universal Credit (UC) was an example of this. The
Council estimated approximately 4,000 children would benefit from
this policy to help to lift children out of poverty.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:left"><span style="">In
conclusion, the Acting Cabinet Member for Finance was confident
they would be able to close the funding gap with measures outlined
which also allowed them to propose a balanced budget for 2026-27
leading to a much more secure financial position in
2027-28.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:36.0pt; text-align:left">
<span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">The Chair invited
witnesses to speak on the agenda item.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:left"><span style="">Simon
Hannah, Assistant Branch Secretary, UNISON, informed the Committee
that:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style=
"border:none windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0cm">&nbsp;</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top:0cm">
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">There was some good
news as the pessimistic predictions on funding from Government had
not materialised, but local government funding was still less than
it had been in 2010 under the last Labour Government.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">The Council needed to
be cautious of the over-reliance on Artificial Intelligence
(AI<span class="GramE">)</span> and he noted that recent research
had revealed that between 70% and &nbsp;...&nbsp; <a href=
"mgAi.aspx?ID=67071" title=
"Link to view the full item text for item 3., Budget and Medium-Term Finance Strategy">
view the full minutes text for item 3.</a></span></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div> 
					
